1
00:01:14,451 --> 00:01:16,327
未来
The future.

2
00:01:16,411 --> 00:01:19,831
一个黑暗 孤寂的世界
A dark, desolate world.

3
00:01:25,712 --> 00:01:31,009
战争 苦难 死亡
A world of war, suffering, loss...

4
00:01:31,301 --> 00:01:33,219
笼罩着双方
on both sides.

5
00:01:34,345 --> 00:01:38,808
变种人和挺身而出帮助他们的人类
Mutants and the humans who dared to help them.

6
00:01:42,228 --> 00:01:46,441
都在抵抗一个无法战胜的敌人
Fighting an enemy we cannot defeat.

7
00:02:13,301 --> 00:02:16,221
这是我们不可避免的命运吗
Are we destined down this path?

8
00:02:16,596 --> 00:02:21,768
和曾经无数种物种一样 走上自取灭亡的道路
Destined to destroy ourselves like so many species before us?

9
00:02:25,396 --> 00:02:29,150
还是及时进化 以求改变自我
Or can we evolve fast enough to change ourselves?

10
00:02:29,776 --> 00:02:31,152
改变命运
Change our fate?

11
00:02:37,367 --> 00:02:40,745
未来是否真是定数
Is the future truly set?

12
00:04:10,209 --> 00:04:11,252
它们来了 
They're here!

13
00:04:17,008 --> 00:04:18,051
来不及了
Time's up.

14
00:04:18,176 --> 00:04:19,218
哨兵
Sentinels!

15
00:04:23,431 --> 00:04:24,474
太阳黑子
Sunspot!

16
00:04:29,437 --> 00:04:30,563
快走吧
Let's go.

17
00:05:19,529 --> 00:05:20,822
快跑
Run!

18
00:05:22,532 --> 00:05:23,533
快走
Go!

19
00:07:04,258 --> 00:07:06,010
闪烁 不
Blink! No!

20
00:07:53,182 --> 00:07:54,600
你来晚了 混蛋
Too late, assholes.

21
00:08:14,203 --> 00:08:15,746
不许动 你这个变种人渣滓
Don't move, you mutant scum!

22
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:20,626
不
No!

23
00:08:22,003 --> 00:08:24,213
趴在地上 双手放在头后面
Flat on the ground, hands behind your head!

24
00:08:29,135 --> 00:08:31,762
我们的人所剩无几
So few of us left.

25
00:08:35,141 --> 00:08:36,183
教授
Professor?

26
00:08:37,476 --> 00:08:38,728
找到了
I've found them.

27
00:10:11,028 --> 00:10:12,154
教授
Professor!

28
00:10:14,198 --> 00:10:15,408
鲍比
嗨 暴风女
Bobby.
Hey, Storm.

29
00:10:16,534 --> 00:10:17,576
嗨 小子
Hey, kid.

30
00:10:18,577 --> 00:10:21,122
教授 你来了
Professor, you made it.

31
00:10:43,853 --> 00:10:46,814
每次哨兵来袭 战戟都会发现它们
Whenever the Sentinels attack, Warpath spots them...

32
00:10:47,481 --> 00:10:49,316
我送毕肖普回到袭击发生前
then I send Bishop back to warn us

33
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,901
去警告我们
of the attack before it happens.

34
00:10:51,569 --> 00:10:53,863
让闪烁去找新的藏身处
Blink scouts the next site...

35
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:56,949
这样在它们找来之前我们就不在了
and then we leave before they ever know we were there.

36
00:10:57,116 --> 00:10:59,744
因为 我们就没在过
Because... we never were.

37
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:01,746
什么叫你们就没在过
What do you mean you were never there?

38
00:11:01,912 --> 00:11:03,330
她让毕肖普回到袭击发生的
She projects Bishop back in time

39
00:11:03,414 --> 00:11:04,957
前几天去警告他们
a few days to warn the others...

40
00:11:05,124 --> 00:11:06,751
未来的袭击
of the coming attack.

41
00:11:06,917 --> 00:11:09,044
她能让毕肖普回到过去
So she sends Bishop back in time?

42
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:11,839
只是让他的意识回到他的过去
No, just his consciousness, into his younger self.

43
00:11:12,006 --> 00:11:13,257
过去的身体里
His younger body.

44
00:11:14,049 --> 00:11:15,217
喔
Wow.

45
00:11:15,926 --> 00:11:19,013
这也许行得通 查尔斯
This might just work, Charles.

46
00:11:20,139 --> 00:11:21,307
什么行得通
What might work?

47
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:27,104
哨兵计划最早是由玻利瓦尔·崔斯克博士提出的
The Sentinel program was originally conceived by Doctor Bolivar Trask.

48
00:11:27,438 --> 00:11:31,901
他是70年代初期 世界顶尖的武器设计专家
In the early '70s, he was one of the world's leading weapons designers.

49
00:11:32,151 --> 00:11:36,363
暗地里 他却在变种人身上进行着实验
But, covertly, he had begun experimenting on mutants...

50
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,700
利用他们的能力完成他的研究
using their gifts to fuel his own research.

51
00:11:39,867 --> 00:11:41,243
这真是不可思议
This is extraordinary.

52
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:44,622
有一个变种人发现了他的研究内容
There was one mutant who had discovered what he was doing.

53
00:11:44,914 --> 00:11:49,627
这家伙 可以随心所欲地变成 任何人
A mutant with the ability to transform herself into anyone.

54
00:11:50,127 --> 00:11:51,545
魔形女
Mystique.

55
00:11:52,421 --> 00:11:54,507
我认识的她叫瑞雯
I knew her as Raven.

56
00:11:54,715 --> 00:11:56,133
我们从小相识
We met when we were children,

57
00:11:56,217 --> 00:11:58,052
一起长大
grew up together.

58
00:11:58,928 --> 00:12:00,721
她就像是我的妹妹
She was like a sister to me.

59
00:12:01,055 --> 00:12:02,765
我想帮助她
I tried to help her...

60
00:12:02,932 --> 00:12:06,477
没想到把她越推越远
but only succeeded in driving her away.

61
00:12:07,186 --> 00:12:10,064
她走遍世界 追杀崔斯克
She hunted Trask across the world.

62
00:12:10,397 --> 00:12:13,692
战争结束后 在1973年的巴黎会议上
And at the Paris Peace Accords in 1973,

63
00:12:13,776 --> 00:12:15,027
越南战争后
after the Vietnam War...

64
00:12:15,861 --> 00:12:17,238
她找到了崔斯克
she found Trask...

65
00:12:20,324 --> 00:12:21,867
杀死了他
and killed him.

66
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,750
那是她第一次杀人
It was the first time she killed.

67
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:31,460
但不是最后一次
It wasn't her last.

68
00:12:31,627 --> 00:12:35,381
崔斯克的死并没有导致她想要的结果
But killing Trask did not have the outcome she expected.

69
00:12:35,506 --> 00:12:37,299
反而在一定程度上刺激了政府对
It only persuaded the government

70
00:12:37,383 --> 00:12:39,552
哨兵计划的需求
of the need for his program.

71
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:41,929
他们当场抓住了她
They captured her that day...

72
00:12:42,096 --> 00:12:44,890
折磨她 在她身上做实验
tortured her, experimented on her.

73
00:12:46,016 --> 00:12:50,437
他们在她的DNA里发现了她具有变形能力的秘密
In her DNA, they discovered the secrets to her powers of transformation.

74
00:12:50,604 --> 00:12:52,648
从此 他们就掌握了
It gave them the key they needed...

75
00:12:52,773 --> 00:12:56,777
制造能应对任何变种能力的武器的关键所在
to create weapons that could adapt to any mutant power.

76
00:12:57,236 --> 00:12:59,196
只用了不到50年
And in less than 50 years...

77
00:12:59,363 --> 00:13:01,532
那种屠杀了我们众多同胞的
the machines that have destroyed...

78
00:13:01,657 --> 00:13:04,618
机器就诞生了
so many of our kind were created.

79
00:13:05,536 --> 00:13:09,248
一切都始于1973年的那一天
But it all started that day in 1973...

80
00:13:09,707 --> 00:13:11,125
她第一次杀人那天
the day she first killed.

81
00:13:11,375 --> 00:13:13,335
那天 她彻底变成了
The day she truly became...

82
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:14,879
魔形女
Mystique.

83
00:13:16,922 --> 00:13:18,299
你想回到那一天
You want to go back there.

84
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:21,760
如果我能找到她 阻止她杀人
If I can get to her, stop the assassination...

85
00:13:21,886 --> 00:13:23,304
不让她落入敌手
keep her out of their hands...

86
00:13:23,429 --> 00:13:26,891
便能将哨兵计划扼杀在摇篮之中
then we can stop the Sentinels from ever being born.

87
00:13:27,016 --> 00:13:30,227
让这场战争还没开始就结束
And end this war before it ever begins.

88
00:13:34,523 --> 00:13:37,318
我可以送一个人回到几星期前
Uh, I can send someone back a couple weeks.

89
00:13:37,943 --> 00:13:39,236
也许一个月前
Maybe a month.

90
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:42,573
可你要我送你回几十年前
But you're talking about going back decades.

91
00:13:42,698 --> 00:13:45,576
教授 你拥有世界上最强的大脑
You have the most powerful brain in the world, Professor...

92
00:13:46,285 --> 00:13:49,914
但是到了极限 它一样会崩溃
but the mind can only stretch so far before it snaps.

93
00:13:50,456 --> 00:13:53,542
你会被撕成碎片 对不起
It would rip you apart. I'm sorry.

94
00:13:53,918 --> 00:13:55,878
没人能承受这趟时空旅行
No one could survive that trip.

95
00:13:56,253 --> 00:13:59,256
如果是一个大脑能自我修复的人呢
What if someone's mind has a way of snapping back?

96
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:03,427
一个即使被撕裂也能痊愈的人呢
What if someone can heal as fast as they're ripped apart?

97
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,595
这太冒险
It's a risk.

98
00:14:04,678 --> 00:14:05,930
我知道
Yeah, I'm getting that.

99
00:14:06,013 --> 00:14:07,723
不只是对你
Not just for you.

100
00:14:07,806 --> 00:14:10,184
你这样 改变历史
You do this, you change history.

101
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:11,435
那是意义所在
Well, that's kind of the point.

102
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:13,771
我们中的某些人可能被杀
Some of us could be killed.

103
00:14:13,854 --> 00:14:16,065
某些人可能永远不会出生
Some of us may never be born.

104
00:14:16,148 --> 00:14:18,484
我们根本不能预料世界会产生什么改变
We have no idea how things may change.

105
00:14:18,817 --> 00:14:20,527
我们还能继续坚持
We could keep going.

106
00:14:20,694 --> 00:14:22,237
坚持反抗
Keep fighting.

107
00:14:22,446 --> 00:14:23,614
直到何时
Until what?

108
00:14:25,157 --> 00:14:27,660
你们得做出抉择
You've got a decision to make.

109
00:14:27,743 --> 00:14:29,787
你们可以继续送毕肖普回到过去
You can keep sending Bishop back in time

110
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,914
反复地警告你们
over and over again to warn you,

111
00:14:31,997 --> 00:14:36,043
直到某一天他失败了 你们也跟着丧生
until one day, he doesn't make it, and you all die.

112
00:14:36,126 --> 00:14:38,045
或者你们放弃这次生命
Or you can give up this life.

113
00:14:38,128 --> 00:14:40,798
那样他们和在这场战争中丧生的所有人
So that they and everyone else who died in this war

114
00:14:40,881 --> 00:14:42,883
都能拥有未来
can actually have a future.

115
00:14:42,967 --> 00:14:45,427
你是在要求我们把我们的生命牺牲给
You're asking us to sacrifice our lives

116
00:14:45,511 --> 00:14:47,596
一个我们也许完全不曾存在的未来
for a future we might not even be a part of.

117
00:14:47,763 --> 00:14:48,973
就是这样
Yes.

118
00:14:49,306 --> 00:14:51,016
第二次机会
A second chance.

119
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:54,436
每个人的更好的机会
A better chance for everyone.

120
00:14:59,984 --> 00:15:01,318
我的人手需要投票
My people need to vote.

121
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:06,573
他们刚刚投过了
They just did.

122
00:15:07,825 --> 00:15:09,034
算上他们
They're in.

123
00:15:27,344 --> 00:15:28,679
好了 大家散开
Okay, spread out.

124
00:15:28,804 --> 00:15:31,015
各就各位
Take your positions.

125
00:15:44,987 --> 00:15:47,573
我回到过去不知道在哪里的身体里
So I wake up in my younger body, God knows where.

126
00:15:47,656 --> 00:15:48,866
然后呢
Then what?

127
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:52,036
你去我家找我 说服我
You'll need to go to my house and find me.

128
00:15:52,202 --> 00:15:54,788
让我相信你说的那些事
Convince me of all of this.

129
00:15:54,872 --> 00:15:56,582
你不能直接读心吗
Won't you be able to just read my mind?

130
00:15:56,707 --> 00:15:59,877
1973年的我没有这种能力
I didn't have my powers in 1973.

131
00:16:00,210 --> 00:16:04,381
罗根 我曾经为你做的事 现在你要为我做了
Logan, you're going to have to do for me what I once did for you.

132
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:07,342
指引我 引领我
Lead me, guide me.

133
00:16:07,676 --> 00:16:09,970
那个与现在截然不同的我
I was a very different man then.

134
00:16:10,095 --> 00:16:12,264
你要对我有耐心
You'll have to be patient with me.

135
00:16:13,057 --> 00:16:15,559
我最擅长耐心了
Patience is my strongest suit.

136
00:16:15,726 --> 00:16:17,895
你还要去找我
什么
You'll need me as well.
What?

137
00:16:18,062 --> 00:16:20,814
魔形女离开查尔斯之后来找了我
After Mystique left Charles, she came with me...

138
00:16:20,898 --> 00:16:24,026
是我使她走上了这条危险的路
and I set her on a dangerous path.

139
00:16:24,359 --> 00:16:25,652
黑暗的路
A darker path.

140
00:16:25,736 --> 00:16:28,405
你得让当年分道扬镳
It's going to take the two of us, side by side...

141
00:16:28,489 --> 00:16:31,200
恩断义绝的我们携手合作
at a time when we couldn't be further apart.

142
00:16:34,578 --> 00:16:35,913
好主意
Great.

143
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:38,415
我要去哪里找你
So where do I find you?

144
00:16:38,749 --> 00:16:40,250
这有点复杂
Well, it's complicated.

145
00:16:41,752 --> 00:16:43,796
你真的决定要这样做
Are you sure about this?

146
00:16:45,422 --> 00:16:47,007
不只是他的能力受到考验
It's not just his power that'll be tested.

147
00:16:47,091 --> 00:16:49,218
我知道这会对你造成什么影响
I've seen what this can do to you.

148
00:16:50,636 --> 00:16:51,762
我能应对
I can handle this.

149
00:16:52,262 --> 00:16:53,764
相信我
Trust me.

150
00:16:56,308 --> 00:16:58,644
我猜我们要在来世相见了
I guess I'll see you in the next life.

151
00:17:13,617 --> 00:17:15,160
当你的意识回到过去的时候
Basically, your body will go to sleep

152
00:17:15,244 --> 00:17:17,621
身体就会陷入沉睡
while your mind travels back in time.

153
00:17:17,704 --> 00:17:22,000
在这段时间 你的过去和现在是平行共存的
As long as you're back there, past and present will continue to coexist.

154
00:17:22,459 --> 00:17:23,794
一旦你醒过来
But once you wake up...

155
00:17:25,129 --> 00:17:27,840
你过去的作为就会覆盖历史
whatever you've done will take hold and become history.

156
00:17:28,132 --> 00:17:31,051
而我们将只记得被改变后的历史
And for the rest of us, it will be the only history that we know.

157
00:17:31,135 --> 00:17:34,513
过去的50年就将会不复存在
It will be like the last 50 years never happened.

158
00:17:34,972 --> 00:17:37,182
这个时空 这场战争
And this world, and this war...

159
00:17:37,349 --> 00:17:40,727
记得这一切的将只有你一个人
the only person who will remember it is you.

160
00:17:42,604 --> 00:17:43,605
好了 罗根
All right, Logan...

161
00:17:43,689 --> 00:17:45,315
现在你要清空思绪
I need you to clear your head

162
00:17:45,399 --> 00:17:46,900
你要尽可能地保持平静
and to stay as calm as possible.

163
00:17:46,984 --> 00:17:48,485
什么 什么意思
What? What do you mean?

164
00:17:48,569 --> 00:17:50,946
如果你的意识过于波动 我会控制不住你
If your mind gets rocky, it will be harder for me to hold you...

165
00:17:51,029 --> 00:17:53,407
你会掉进过去和未来的间隙里
and you could start to slip between past and future.

166
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:55,492
如果我有点小情绪呢
What if I need to get a little rocky?

167
00:17:56,618 --> 00:17:57,911
想想平和的事
Think peaceful thoughts?

168
00:17:57,995 --> 00:18:00,914
平和的事 有好消息吗
Peaceful thoughts... Do you have any good news?

169
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:04,918
喔 因为你不会变老 所以外貌不会改变
Well, you don't really age, so you'll pretty much look the same.

170
00:18:06,003 --> 00:18:07,921
你能在过去停留的时间不多
You won't have much time in the past.

171
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:09,631
哨兵会找到我们
The Sentinels will find us.

172
00:18:09,715 --> 00:18:11,049
每次都能
They always do.

173
00:18:11,216 --> 00:18:12,843
这次我们将无路可逃
And this time, we won't be able to run.

174
00:18:13,010 --> 00:18:14,553
只能坐以待毙
We'll have no escape.

175
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:17,890
这是最后的机会了
This is our last chance.

176
00:18:18,348 --> 00:18:22,186
你确定这事能成
是啊 我相信他
You really think this will work?
I have faith in him.

177
00:18:22,352 --> 00:18:24,229
我担心的不是他 是我们
It's not him I'm worried about, it's us.

178
00:18:24,354 --> 00:18:25,856
年轻的我们
We were young...

179
00:18:25,939 --> 00:18:27,524
还那么无知
we didn't know any better.

180
00:18:28,525 --> 00:18:31,028
现在不会了
We will now.

181
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:33,405
回头见
See you all soon.

182
00:18:34,281 --> 00:18:36,575
可能会有点疼
This might sting a little.

183
00:19:25,248 --> 00:19:27,960
The first time

184
00:19:30,754 --> 00:19:34,174
Ever I saw your face

185
00:19:35,634 --> 00:19:36,843
喔
Whoa.

186
00:19:41,056 --> 00:19:45,352
I thought the sun

187
00:19:46,895 --> 00:19:47,938
Rose in your eyes

188
00:19:58,073 --> 00:20:03,620
And the moon and the stars

189
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:11,545
Were the gifts you gave

190
00:20:11,628 --> 00:20:13,088
我的天呐
Holy shit.

